article.description: Osiris Eldridge and Dinma Odiakosa scored 12 points each as Illinois State edged Creighton 67-63 on Saturday.
article.headline: Eldridge, Odiakosa help Illinois State edge Creighton
article.linkText: Illinois State pulls out victory against Creighton
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- Osiris Eldridge and Dinma Odiakosa scored 12 points each as Illinois State edged Creighton 67-63 on Saturday. The victory allowed the Redbirds (18-8, 9-6) to move into third place in the Missouri Valley Conference. The Bluejays (13-13, 8-7) lost at home for just the second time this season. There were three ties and 14 lead changes in the second half -- 11 during an 11-minute stretch in which neither team led by more than three. Odiakosa finally broke that string by giving Illinois State a 60-55 advantage with 4:11 to play. The Redbirds extended their lead to seven on a steal and breakaway basket by Lloyd Phillips with 3:47 left. Trailing by two, the Bluejays turned the ball over on their final possession without getting off a shot. Phillips then sealed the game with two free throws. Kenny Lawson had 20 points for Creighton to lead all scorers.
